snippet.textDisplay: At LEAST your parents were health kernels. Mine are health nuts ad I'm still living with them. Literally its a treat  to get honey nut cheerios and I love them. My parents eat the same thing every morning for breakfast: Oatmeal with a banana and dried goji berries and chia seeds and raisins and cranberries and literally our entire dried food cupboard. I think it tastes nasty but my parents still eat it EVERYDAY. I guess I'm grateful for them shoving vegetables down my throat at every meal, but the real problem is I never have anything to snack on. I walk out to my kitchen looking for a snack( even though I know there is probably none), and i open the cupboards and fridge to find yogurt, granola bars. dried fruit, and expired halloween candy cuz my dad hid all of it then forgot about it. But my mother, who takes mercy on me and my brothers, occasionally buys SNACKS. I mean, they are all organic and vegetable based, but some of them actually taste decent. Mk, I'm just ranting now. Also, soda is out of the question.  We are asian too, but instead of white rice we eat BROWN RICE. I know it probably doesn't sound too bad to you guys, but after a few years, you get really sick of it. whelp, byee.
